crystallized ghost.description: It is a ghost underwent some kind of reaction during a Spirit Storage Explosion, and now it's been a Crystallized inside a solid block. Maybe one day Scientists will extract DNA.

warning block.name: Warning Block
warning block.description: When something is so dangerous there's no time for words, just throw down some yellow and black stripes!

warning background.name: Warning Background
warning background.description: When something is so dangerous there's no time for words, just thrown down some yellow and black stripes!

demon control cap.name: Demon Control Cap
demon control cap.description: With this helmet, which is not a colander at all, you can control a demon dog from another dimension!

haunted pants.name: Haunted Pants
haunted pants.description: What's that eerie noise coming from in there? These pants must be haunted!

root beer.name: Root Beer
root beer.description: Ah, a cold frosty mug root beer. The only downside is that all that carbonation is sure to make you burp a tiny bit...

spray tan.name: Spray Tan
spray tan.description: If you don't want to get cancer from the sun, spray this on your skin to get an ultra-realistic bronze tone! Warning: Causes lots and lots of cancer. Lots.

shark-tooth necklace.name: Shark-Tooth Necklace
shark-tooth necklace.description: I don't know if this is a tooth from every shark you've killed, or each one that's bitten you, but either way it's impressive.

firefin.name: Firefin
firefin.description: It's not too tough to figure out where this fish gets it's name. During the winter, they stay in warmer waters, but for the week of Summerfest, these can be found in their old spawning grounds right here in Growtopia!

bone spikes.name: Bone Spikes
bone spikes.description: Someone has stacked a bunch of bones here and sharpened the ends. I know that's dangerous in itself, but aren't you a little more concerned about exactly who did it and where they are now?

ghost charm.name: Ghost Charm
ghost charm.description: When activated (punch to activate), this horrific face terrifies even ghosts, preventing new ghosts from appearing in your world. Ghosts that are already in your world still need to be captured by B.O.O. professionals, however. The poor ghosts are trapped on this earthly plane!

steam funnel.name: Steam Funnel
steam funnel.description: The links up to other Steam blocks and can conduct steam power. Steam can enter this Funnel from 3 sides, but can only exit from one side. You figure out which!

steam funnel - up.name: Steam Funnel - Up
steam funnel - up.description: The links up to other Steam blocks and can conduct steam power. Steam can enter this Funnel from 3 sides, but can only exit from one side. You figure out which!

steam funnel - down.name: Steam Funnel - Down
steam funnel - down.description: The links up to other Steam blocks and can conduct steam power. Steam can enter this Funnel from 3 sides, but can only exit from one side. You figure out which!

b.o.o. sign.name: B.O.O. Sign
b.o.o. sign.description: Advertise your ghost-hunting services with this handy sign! You're a proud member of B.O.O., so let everybody know. Use your wrench to set the message.

shark tooth.name: Shark Tooth
shark tooth.description: Just when you thought it was safe to go back to the shark dentist...

atomic fireball.name: Atomic Fireball
atomic fireball.description: For when lava isn't hot enough!

steam crossover.name: Steam Crossover
steam crossover.description: This links up to other Steam blocks and can conduct steam power. It's actually 2 unconnected pipes - one runs from left to down, and the other runs from up to right. Use this to keep steam from going places you don't want!

steam crank.name: Steam Crank
steam crank.description: This links up to other Steam blocks and can conduct steam power. It's actually 2 unconnected pipes - one runs from left to down, and the other runs from up to right. Use this to keep steam from going places you don't want!

steam lamp.name: Steam Lamp
steam lamp.description: This crystal lamp is powered by steam! It burns for 10 seconds each time it gets charged. It can only be powered from below.

steam spikes.name: Steam Spikes
steam spikes.description: Steam forces razor-shape spikes from the ground in this dastardly trap! It can only be powered from below. Power it again to lower the spikes.

no-face.name: No-Face
no-face.description: Embarrassed? Feel like hiding your face? How about just removing it instead?

purple djellaba.name: Purple Djellaba
purple djellaba.description: This long robe is suitable for male or female Growtopians, provided they want to look snazzy and colorful!

yellow djellaba.name: Yellow Djellaba
yellow djellaba.description: This long robe is suitable for male or female Growtopians, provided they want to look snazzy and colorful!

green djellaba.name: Green Djellaba
green djellaba.description: This long robe is suitable for male or female Growtopians, provided they want to look snazzy and colorful!

mini blocks.name: Mini Blocks
mini blocks.description: These blocks are only 1/4 the size of a normal block! To make up for that, they come in sets of four.

teeny blocks.name: Teeny Blocks
teeny blocks.description: These blocks are only 1/4 the size of Mini Blocks! To make up for that, they come in sets of sixteen.

jigsaw wallpaper.name: Jigsaw Wallpaper
jigsaw wallpaper.description: Well, that was easy... It's a picture of a jigsaw puzzle!

riding broomstick.name: Riding Broomstick
riding broomstick.description: What magic makes this fly? Witch magic makes this fly!

techno visor.name: Techno Visor
techno visor.description: This is handy technology for people who are overwhelmed with modern life - it blocks one of your ears from hearing things, and one of your eyes from seeing things. Just relax and enjoy the left half of the world.

glowstick.name: Glowstick
glowstick.description: This plastic tube of lethal radioactive elements is the perfect thing to swing around at a party! It also provides light.

display shelf.name: Display Shelf
display shelf.description: These are some big shelves. Why not display your favorite items on them? They can hold four items to display.

one-way block.name: One-Way Block
one-way block.description: This block can only be moved through in the direction the arrow is pointing. From the other direction, it might as well be a wall!

vip entrance.name: VIP Entrance
vip entrance.description: The fanciest door in town! The only people getting through this door are the ones who are on The List. Wrench the door to add people to The List. Or remove them, if they have offended you in some way.

rhino horn.name: Rhino Horn
rhino horn.description: Aw, it thinks you're its mama.

globe.name: Globe
globe.description: Add a little class to your office with a globe! You can also wrench it to check the current top worlds.

challenge timer.name: Challenge Timer
challenge timer.description: Player can punch this to begin a challenge: get from the Challenge Start Flag to the Challenge End Flag before the time runs out! Wrench the timer to set up your challenge and insert prizes.

challenge start flag.name: Challenge Start Flag
challenge start flag.description: Use this with a Challenge Timer. Wrench it to set an ID, so it knows which Challenge Timer to work with.

challenge end flag.name: Challenge End Flag
challenge end flag.description: Use this with a Challenge Timer. Wrench it to set an ID, so it knows which Challenge Timer to work with.

fish wall mount.name: Fish Wall Mount
fish wall mount.description: Proud of your catch, but you don't want the responsibility of caring for it? Mount it to this wall plaque with your wrench! You can display Perfect or Massive fish on this mount. Once a fish is mounted, it can never be removed.

octopus head.name: Octopus Head
octopus head.description: This is why aquariums have rules.

stonefish.name: Stonefish
stonefish.description: This is one of the most poisonous fish in the world! It's also made of rock, which is weird.

tamago sushi.name: Tamago Sushi
tamago sushi.description: Wait, this sushi doesn't even have fish in it!

portrait.name: Portrait
portrait.description: Demonstrating your speed-painting skills by painting pictures of anyone in your world in moments! Wrench the portrait to begin painting. It costs 2 of each color of paint for each painting.

orca.name: Orca
orca.description: You could put this in a fish tank, but then people would probably make documentaries about you. Not flattering ones.

red hair dye.name: Red Hair Dye
red hair dye.description: Pour this gunk on your head if you want your hair to be red! It may require multiple applications to achieve the desired color, or mixing with other dyes. The dye interacts with your natural hair color, so some colors may simply be impossible to achieve.

green hair dye.name: Green Hair Dye
green hair dye.description: Pour this gunk on your head if you want your hair to be green! It may require multiple applications to achieve the desired color, or mixing with other dyes. The dye interacts with your natural hair color, so some colors may simply be impossible to achieve.

blue hair dye.name: Blue Hair Dye
blue hair dye.description: Pour this gunk on your head if you want your hair to be blue! It may require multiple applications to achieve the desired color, or mixing with other dyes. The dye interacts with your natural hair color, so some colors may simply be impossible to achieve.

black hair dye.name: Black Hair Dye
black hair dye.description: Pour this gunk on your head if you want your hair to be black! It may require multiple applications to achieve the desired color, or mixing with other dyes. The dye interacts with your natural hair color, so some colors may simply be impossible to achieve.

shampoo.name: Shampoo
shampoo.description: Messed your hair up with dyes? Wash it out with the refreshing scent of lime, coconut, wallaby, and pears. Lather, rinse, and repeat - one bottle might not do the job.

weather machine - stuff.name: Weather Machine - Stuff
weather machine - stuff.description: It's a rainin' stuff! This amazing new weather machine will let you choose any item you have to rain down from the sky! Wrench it to choose your item and adjust other settings. You can only have one of this per world.

beehive.name: Beehive
beehive.description: I feel like this warning is unnecessary, but I'll say it anyway: don't punch a beehive.

honey.name: Honey
honey.description: The sweet nectar of bee spit! Bees also craft plastic bear shapes to store it in. Nobody knows why.

sorcerer stone.name: Sorcerer Stone
sorcerer stone.description: There's mystical gem embedded in this rock. Heck, there's probably a few in there. Smash it open and see!

villain portrait - the harvester.name: Villain Portrait - The Harvester
villain portrait - the harvester.description: Just before knocking him unconscious, you snapped a lovely photo of The Harvester for posterity. Put it up on the wall, show off your achievement!

cosmic power - life harvest.name: Cosmic Power - Life Harvest
cosmic power - life harvest.description: This is a Rare Cosmic Superpower card for use in fighting crime. You can also place it as a block! Cosmic Cards aren't used, they have an effect as long as they are in your hand. Card effect: Heal 1 life every time you inflict more than 1 damage.

super shirt - autumn.name: Super Shirt - Autumn
super shirt - autumn.description: Fight crime in this mighty leafy leotard!

muscle shirt - autumn.name: Muscle Shirt - Autumn
muscle shirt - autumn.description: Flex your muscles in this mighty leafy leotard!

heroic tights - autumn.name: Heroic Tights - Autumn
heroic tights - autumn.description: To be a leafy superhero, you really need to wear tights of some sort.

super tights - autumn.name: Super Tights - Autumn
super tights - autumn.description: To be a leafy superhero, you really need to wear tights of some sort.

heroic boots - autumn.name: Heroic Boots - Autumn
heroic boots - autumn.description: These leafy boots add nothing to your crimefighting skills except to protect you from stray Legos.

super cape - autumn.name: Super Cape - Autumn
super cape - autumn.description: You're no heroman, but it's still pretty swell.

superheroine top - autumn.name: Superheroine Top - Autumn
superheroine top - autumn.description: Flex your muscles in this mighty leafy leotard!

super logo - leaf.name: Super Logo - Leaf
super logo - leaf.description: Emblazon this logo on your super costume to fight crime as... Leaf Lord? Lady Leaf? The Fallen Avenger? It's up to you!

harvest witch mask.name: Harvest Witch Mask
harvest witch mask.description: Normally this mask is only worn during the most profane of dark rituals, beneath a blood red moon. But you can wear it for shopping, parties, whatever!

harvest horn.name: Harvest Horn
harvest horn.description: Don't blow this horn. Never blow this horn. It is evil.

ancestor mooncake.name: Ancestor Mooncake
ancestor mooncake.description: This pastry is filled with a sweet bean paste. An image of your ancestor is imprinted on the top in ancient Growtopian script. Mix this with other Mooncakes in a Laboratory or E-Z Cook Oven to create special Harvest Festival items.

blue hanbok top.name: Blue Hanbok Top
blue hanbok top.description: These Festival clothes are extra festive!

orange hanbok top.name: Orange Hanbok Top
orange hanbok top.description: These Festival clothes are extra festive!

blue hanbok pants.name: Blue Hanbok Pants
blue hanbok pants.description: These Festival clothes are extra festive!

orange hanbok pants.name: Orange Hanbok Pants
orange hanbok pants.description: These Festival clothes are extra festive!

green hanbok skirt.name: Green Hanbok Skirt
green hanbok skirt.description: These Festival clothes are extra festive!

yellow hanbok skirt.name: Yellow Hanbok Skirt
yellow hanbok skirt.description: These Festival clothes are extra festive!

sunflower hair pin.name: Sunflower Hair Pin
sunflower hair pin.description: When sunflowers are out of season, stick this plastic replacement in your hair.

lil' sheepers.name: Lil' Sheepers
lil' sheepers.description: Baa. This little baby sheep will follow you everywhere you go! Mainly because it's tied to your wrist.

sheep.name: Sheep
sheep.description: Baaaaaaa. You can shear a sheep one every few days!

wool.name: Wool
wool.description: This is just a blob of wool. Not too useful. Get 100 of these to weave a bolt together!

wool bolt.name: Wool Bolt
wool bolt.description: Sew wool items by using this in a sewing machine with silk bolts. It takes 3 bolts of silk or wool to craft an item.

harvest robinsons.name: Harvest Robinsons
harvest robinsons.description: These special edition Air Robinsons are themed to celebrate the harvest, or just to be bright crazy colors, like all basketball shoes.

silkworm soul.name: Silkworm Soul
silkworm soul.description: The great thing about silkworms is that they don't have unique souls. They're totally interchangeable! Jam this into any dead silkworm to bring it back for a 2nd chance.

telephone.name: Telephone
telephone.description: It's a phone! Dial it with your wrench. Growtopia doesn't have any cell service, so you're stuck with this old thing.

wooden sword.name: Wooden Sword
wooden sword.description: They use these to train in Kendo. They won't cut much, but getting whacked with one certainly does hurt!

crazy jim.name: Crazy Jim
crazy jim.description: not a real item, just for an icon in the telephone screen.

code block: kappa.name: Code Block: Kappa
code block: kappa.description: This block looks like a mysterious computronic data reference. But that's just for fun, i'm sure. I mean, this is just a game... isn't it?

code block: charlie.name: Code Block: Charlie
code block: charlie.description: This block looks like a mysterious computronic data reference. But that's just for fun, i'm sure. I mean, this is just a game... isn't it?

code block: ouroboros.name: Code Block: Ouroboros
code block: ouroboros.description: This block looks like a mysterious computronic data reference. But that's just for fun, i'm sure. I mean, this is just a game... isn't it?

code block: edamame.name: Code Block: Edamame
code block: edamame.description: This block looks like a mysterious computronic data reference. But that's just for fun, i'm sure. I mean, this is just a game... isn't it?

wool scarf.name: Wool Scarf
wool scarf.description: Your neck is toasty warm. Maybe you should put some pants on too.

sheep shears.name: Sheep Shears
sheep shears.description: This handy tool is alot more effective at cutting wool than your fingers are, so you can get twice as much when you use it to shear a sheep!

illuminati stone.name: Illuminati Stone
illuminati stone.description: Finally, the 100% undeniable proof! You have DISCOVERED THE TRUTH!

fossil rock.name: Fossil Rock
fossil rock.description: This rock seems to have a fossil embedded in it. Maybe you could crack it loose if you tap very carefully with a Rock Hammer.

fossil boulder.name: Fossil Boulder
fossil boulder.description: This rock seems to have a fossil embedded in it. Maybe you could crack it loose if you tap very carefully with a Rock Hammer.

deep fossil rock.name: Deep Fossil Rock
deep fossil rock.description: This rock seems to have a fossil embedded in it. Maybe you could crack it loose if you tap very carefully with a Rock Hammer.

fossilroid.name: Fossilroid
fossilroid.description: This rock seems to have a fossil embedded in it. Maybe you could crack it loose if you tap very carefully with a Rock Hammer.

alien fossil rock.name: Alien Fossil Rock
alien fossil rock.description: This rock seems to have a fossil embedded in it. Maybe you could crack it loose if you tap very carefully with a Rock Hammer.

igneous fossil rock.name: Igneous Fossil Rock
igneous fossil rock.description: This rock seems to have a fossil embedded in it. Maybe you could crack it loose if you tap very carefully with a Rock Hammer.

igneous rock.name: Igneous Rock
igneous rock.description: Igneous rock is formed through the cooling and solidification of magma or lava.

rock hammer.name: Rock Hammer
rock hammer.description: A precision instrument for chipping fossils out of rocks. If you find a fossil, equip this hammer and start tapping, - but do it *carefully!* If the fossil comes loose and you hit it again, you'll break it!

rock chisel.name: Rock Chisel
rock chisel.description: So you've extracted a fossil from a rock, but the rock is still in your way. That's where the chisel comes in! It lets you chip away the rock without damaging the fossil.

fossil.name: Fossil
fossil.description: A corpse from millions of years ago, turned to stone. It's still covered with a lot of stone, so we're not sure what it is just yet. Try cleaning it off in a Fossil Prep Station.

fossil prep station.name: Fossil Prep Station
fossil prep station.description: Put a fossil in this tank where special solvents and bacterial agents will slowly dissolve any remaining rock and reveal exactly what you've found. The time required varies anywhere from an hour to a day depending on how much needs dissolving. The light turns green when it's ready, so punch to collect!

ammonite block.name: Ammonite Block
ammonite block.description: A huge beautiful ammonite fossil has been extracted! It'd make a lovely coffee table.

dino ribcage.name: Dino Ribcage
dino ribcage.description: It's a bit grisly, but these enormous bones make kind of a fun set of monkey bars.

dinosaur mask.name: Dinosaur Mask
dinosaur mask.description: This is how you would look if a dinosaur snuck up behind you and swallowed you, but you got stuck in its throat. It's a really bad situation for everybody involved.

ancient plant seed.name: Ancient Plant Seed
ancient plant seed.description: This seed from the ancient past is completely intact - there may still be some DNA inside! Plant DNA, but still that`s exciting, right?

amber block.name: Amber Block
amber block.description: This ancient tree sap has hardened into a beautiful crystal. Who knows, there might even be a mosquito inside holding dinosaur DNA! That's pretty standard for amber.

t-rex skull.name: T-Rex Skull
t-rex skull.description: This would make an impressive display in your museum! Even more impressive in your haunted house.

red pet pteranodon.name: Red Pet Pteranodon
red pet pteranodon.description: You've brought a dinosaur back to life with genetic engineering! There's no way that this could go badly!

red pet pterosaurus.name: Red Pet Pterosaurus
red pet pterosaurus.description: You've brought a dinosaur back to life with genetic engineering! There's no way that this could go badly!

grey pet tyranodon.description: You've brought a dinosaur back to life with genetic engineering! There's no way that this could go badly!

grey pet tyranopatos.name: Grey Pet Tyranopatos
grey pet tyranopatos.description: You've brought a dinosaur back to life with genetic engineering! There's no way that this could go badly!

grey pet tyrannosaurus.name: Grey Pet Tyrannosaurus
grey pet tyrannosaurus.description: You've brought a dinosaur back to life with genetic engineering! There's no way that this could go badly!

grey pet tyranotops.name: Grey Pet Tyranotops
grey pet tyranotops.description: You've brought a dinosaur back to life with genetic engineering! There's no way that this could go badly!

grey pet triceradon.name: Grey Pet Triceradon
grey pet triceradon.description: You've brought a dinosaur back to life with genetic engineering! There's no way that this could go badly!

grey pet tripatosaurus.name: Grey Pet Tripatosaurus
grey pet tripatosaurus.description: You've brought a dinosaur back to life with genetic engineering! There's no way that this could go badly!

grey pet tricerus rex.name: Grey Pet Tricerus Rex
grey pet tricerus rex.description: You've brought a dinosaur back to life with genetic engineering! There's no way that this could go badly!

grey pet triceratops.name: Grey Pet Triceratops
grey pet triceratops.description: You've brought a dinosaur back to life with genetic engineering! There's no way that this could go badly!

dna processor.name: DNA Processor
dna processor.description: This advanced device from Growtech can take in strands of ancient DNA and combine them to create real living creatures. It has terrifying ethical implications.

dino dna strand a-273.name: Dino DNA Strand A-273
dino dna strand a-273.description: This is a strand of prehistoric DNA. All we know for sure is it comes from a dinosaur. Perhaps there's a way to recombine it and bring them back! That doesn't seem like a terrible idea at all.

dino dna strand c-904.name: Dino DNA Strand C-904
dino dna strand c-904.description: This is a strand of prehistoric DNA. All we know for sure is it comes from a dinosaur. Perhaps there's a way to recombine it and bring them back! That doesn't seem like a terrible idea at all.

dino dna strand g-137.name: Dino DNA Strand G-137
dino dna strand g-137.description: This is a strand of prehistoric DNA. All we know for sure is it comes from a dinosaur. Perhaps there's a way to recombine it and bring them back! That doesn't seem like a terrible idea at all.

dino dna strand t-658.name: Dino DNA Strand T-658
dino dna strand t-658.description: This is a strand of prehistoric DNA. All we know for sure is it comes from a dinosaur. Perhaps there's a way to recombine it and bring them back! That doesn't seem like a terrible idea at all.

plant dna strand x-277.name: Plant DNA Strand X-277
plant dna strand x-277.description: This is a strand of prehistoric DNA. All we know for sure is it comes from a plant. Perhaps there's a way to recombine it and bring them back! That actually sounds pretty safe, since it's a plant.

plant dna strand y-985.name: Plant DNA Strand Y-985
plant dna strand y-985.description: This is a strand of prehistoric DNA. All we know for sure is it comes from a plant. Perhaps there's a way to recombine it and bring them back! That actually sounds pretty safe, since it's a plant.

prehistoric red fern.name: Prehistoric Red Fern
prehistoric red fern.description: It's sad to think where this grows.

purple devourer plant.name: Purple Devourer Plant
purple devourer plant.description: This is what happens when you give a prehistoric flower a taste for magic bacon!

blue devourer plant.name: Blue Devourer Plant
blue devourer plant.description: This is what happens when you give a prehistoric flower a taste for magic bacon!

prehistoric vines.name: Prehistoric Vines
prehistoric vines.description: You can hide from rampaging dinosaurs in these vines.

prehistoric candy vines.name: Prehistoric Candy Vines
prehistoric candy vines.description: You can try to hide from rampaging dinosaurs in these vines, but you'll probably get eaten because the vines themselves taste like candy.

seussian tree.name: Seussian Tree
seussian tree.description: These particular trees, near the Jirassic seas, produced quite a crunchety fruit. Though scientists say that it tasted okay, we can't pollinate so it's moot.

flowersaurus rex.name: Flowersaurus Rex
flowersaurus rex.description: You monster, what fresh horror have you wrought?!!? Has science gone too far?

blue riding raptor.name: Blue Riding Raptor
blue riding raptor.description: I know, they're supposed to have feathers and stuff nowadays... Well, this is an old-school raptor!

brown riding raptor.name: Brown Riding Raptor
brown riding raptor.description: I know, they're supposed to have feathers and stuff nowadays... Well, this is an old-school raptor!

red riding raptor.name: Red Riding Raptor
red riding raptor.description: I know, they're supposed to have feathers and stuff nowadays... Well, this is an old-school raptor!

golden riding raptor.name: Golden Riding Raptor
golden riding raptor.description: I think this raptor has more World Locks than you do.

raptor dna strand alpha.name: Raptor DNA Strand Alpha
raptor dna strand alpha.description: This is a strand of prehistoric DNA. It appears to be the beginning of a velociraptor DNA sequence. Perhaps there's a way to recombine it and bring them back! That doesn't seem like a terrible idea at all.

raptor dna strand omega.name: Raptor DNA Strand Omega
raptor dna strand omega.description: This is a strand of prehistoric DNA. It appears to be the tail end of a velociraptor DNA sequence. Perhaps there's a way to recombine it and bring them back! That doesn't seem like a terrible idea at all.

dna extractor.name: DNA Extractor
dna extractor.description: This experimental device can extract prehistoric DNA from objects which contain even small traces. To give it a try, just use an item on it and see what you find! THis is very new technology, so results are unpredictable, and rarely successful.

stone spear.name: Stone Spear
stone spear.description: In ancient times, sticks and stones were about as good as it got. The upside is it's a magic stone - this spear will teleport back into your hand once thrown!

blue hardhat.name: Blue Hardhat
blue hardhat.description: Head protection is required in construction areas, and at some dig sites.

outback hat.name: Outback Hat
outback hat.description: G'day! Barbie! Shrimp! That's not a knife, it's a hat! These hats are popular among paleontologists and other desert dwellers.

fossil brush.name: Fossil Brush
fossil brush.description: You can use this to gently brush a fossil before you pick it up, improving its quality. A Fossil Brush will be destroyed upon use (fossils are very rough until you brush them!). If you pick up a fossil, your finger oils will make a Fossil Brush useless, so be sure you brush before collecting!

polished fossil.name: Polished Fossil
polished fossil.description: This fossil has been carefully polished, so it's sure to yield something good when run through a Fossil Prep Station!

doompunk corset.name: Doompunk Corset
doompunk corset.description: Internal organs rotted away? The corset should fit you fine!

doompunk skirt.name: Doompunk Skirt
doompunk skirt.description: Multiple layers of petticoats keep you warm when stalking your prey!

doompunk top hat.name: Doompunk Top Hat
doompunk top hat.description: Keep an extra pair of goggles up there. You never know when you'll need them for evil.

doompunk waistcoat.name: Doompunk Waistcoat
doompunk waistcoat.description: The perfect garment for housing a pocketwatch, monocle, and perhaps poison needles. Definitely some evil stuff in those pockets.

doompunk leggings.name: Doompunk Leggings
doompunk leggings.description: Works equally well for a doompunk or a pirate! Or maybe a serial killer from the 80's.

doompunk trenchcoat.name: Doompunk Trenchcoat
doompunk trenchcoat.description: Keep warm while stalking people on those frosty London evenings in this stylish piece of Grow Couture! Note: this is a "chest item", like a necklace so you can wear any shirts and back items you want underneath it.

eye of growganoth.name: Eye Of Growganoth
eye of growganoth.description: This accursed necklace binds one of the eternal and innumerable Eyes of Growganoth to your service. Just make sure you don't take *your* eye off of it - at the first sign of weakness, it will devour your soul!

apocalypse steed.name: Apocalypse Steed
apocalypse steed.description: The four horsemen have updated to more modern steeds. They're probably gonna be pretty mad when they find out you have swiped one.

jack o' lantern mask.name: Jack o' Lantern Mask
jack o' lantern mask.description: Luckily this is just latex and not actually a gooey carved-out pumpkin.

buzzsaw.name: Buzzsaw
buzzsaw.description: This is how your shop teacher lost those fingers.

rickety wallpaper.name: Rickety Wallpaper
rickety wallpaper.description: So this is what the inside of a haunted house looks like!

rickety window.name: Rickety Window
rickety window.description: So this is what the inside of a haunted house looks like! Plus, you can see outside of it from here.

rickety door.name: Rickety Door
rickety door.description: Finally, your chance to escape this haunted house! Wrench the door to set the destination.

death's scythe.name: Death's Scythe
death's scythe.description: Careful where you swing that thing.

demon chariot.name: Demon Chariot
demon chariot.description: This thing goes pretty fast for a vehicle with only 2 horsepower.

logarithmic wheel.name: Logarithmic Wheel
logarithmic wheel.description: You know what a really good weapon is? A wagon wheel. Yeah, I mean... yeah.

demonic skull.name: Demonic Skull
demonic skull.description: Just the thing for showing your appreciation of the darker musicks.

steel spike.name: Steel Spike
steel spike.description: Hey, these things have a million uses! I can't think of any right now, but they totally do. Just don't leave them inside surgical patients, please.

tempered steel spike.name: Tempered Steel Spike
tempered steel spike.description: This spike is so much shinier now! Classy enough to wear to the Halloween Ball.

spiked collar.name: Spiked Collar
spiked collar.description: Ah yeah, you look tough, like a junkyard dog.

malevolent hair.name: Malevolent Hair
malevolent hair.description: What are you up to under that mop-top? Seems like something a little sneaky..

riding raven.name: Riding Raven
riding raven.description: Only dark magic could breed a raven so massive. It`s so powerful it allows you to double-jump!

haunted darkness.name: Haunted Darkness
haunted darkness.description: It's pitch-black inside this haunted house! Players can only see what's on this tile if it's in their line of sight, or they have special tools.

haunted window.name: Haunted Window
haunted window.description: It's so dark in here, only the window provides any relief! Players can only see what's on this tile if it's in their line of sight, or they have special tools.

haunted door.name: Haunted Door
haunted door.description: Finally, your chance to escape this haunted house! Wrench the door to set up a creepy question player must answer to go through.

sheet music: spooky.name: Sheet Music: Spooky
sheet music: spooky.description: If you aren't in range of a boombox, this will play a spooky sound for you. There are 14 different sounds, depending where you place it vertically. Try them all!

stone pagoda.name: Stone Pagoda
stone pagoda.description: There's no better place for a Grand Tournament than in a pagoda!

master peng stonework.name: Master Peng Stonework
master peng stonework.description: Isn't Master Peng awesome? This stonework blends in with Stone Pagoda blocks.

paper wall.name: Paper Wall
paper wall.description: This wallpaper is a paper wall.

stone pagoda roof element.name: Stone Pagoda Roof Element
stone pagoda roof element.description: Stick this at the ends of your pagoda roofs.It doesn't serve any functional purpose, but it does sure nice. Just make sure you put it the right way or it'll be floating in midair.

decorative roof dragon.name: Decorative Roof Dragon
decorative roof dragon.description: Just for looks. Make your pagoda roofs spikey with dragons! Not so spikey they hurt, though.

grand jade platform.name: Grand Jade Platform
grand jade platform.description: Something stylish to stand on. Try decorating it with Decorative Roof Dragons!

stone pagoda base.name: Stone Pagoda Base
stone pagoda base.description: This is a special piece - it looks like the bottom row of a Stone Pagoda, and it even tiles properly with Stone Pagoda blocks. The trick is, it won't tile with the ones below it. Use it to put a roof in the middle of your pagoda! Kind of a key feature of pagodas, right? It will also tile with Decorative Roof Dragons.

master peng.name: Master Peng
master peng.description: Master Peng runs The Grand Tournament. Don't mess with him. But punching is how he likes to be greeted, so one punch is cool.

tourney token.name: Tourney Token
tourney token.description: Your reward for victory in The Grand Tournament. Put it in the Prize Ladder to win fabulous prizes!

wooden pagoda wall.name: Wooden Pagoda Wall
wooden pagoda wall.description: For a warmer look to your pagoda, try wood. Also, you can walk in front of it, which stone is less forgiving about.

wooden pagoda door.name: Wooden Pagoda Door
wooden pagoda door.description: Like any door, you can wrench it to set the destination.

wooden pagoda roof.name: Wooden Pagoda Roof
wooden pagoda roof.description: This is a roof for your wooden pagoda. Unlike the Wooden Pagoda Wall, this is solid, so it's safe to stand on.

prize ladder.name: Prize Ladder
prize ladder.description: Players can put Tourney Tokens in here to push their luck in winning prizes.

tournament ticket.name: Tournament Ticket
tournament ticket.description: This ticket allows you entry into one Grand Tournament. Visit Master Peng in the world TOURNAMENT to enter the tournament. You can battle as many times as you wish in the current tournament, but when it ends, your ticket will self-destruct.

punched tournament ticket.name: Punched Tournament Ticket
punched tournament ticket.description: Your ticket has been punched! You can battle in the current Tournament as many times as you like. The ticket will self-destruct when the tournament ends. Don't lose it, or you can't battle anymore!

snack fu.name: Snack Fu
snack fu.description: Master Ping, Master Peng's brother, runs Snack Fu, providing delicious and exotic treats to everybody watching the tournament!

ramune.name: Ramune
ramune.description: This fizzy lemon-lime drink is sure to result in some major burps.

pow stones.name: Pow Stones
pow stones.description: This carbonated candy crackles and pops in your mouth. Don't worry, it's probably not made from real rocks. Warning: DO NOT COMBINE WITH SODA. Super duper true urban legends verify that this is dangerous.

extractium ore.name: Extractium Ore
extractium ore.description: This mysterious element has strange properties which seem to make DNA extraction more successful!

extractium shard.name: Extractium Shard
extractium shard.description: This mysterious element seems to be present in small quantities in ancient fossils. Maybe you can combine these shards into a piece large enough to have a measurable effect on something!

tournament banner.name: Tournament Banner
tournament banner.description: Wrench this to find out key info about the Grand Tournament!

jade portcullis.name: Jade Portcullis
jade portcullis.description: Look out the ruffians with this decorative gateway.

weather machine - pagoda.name: Weather Machine - Pagoda
weather machine - pagoda.description: Wow, it's pagoda season already? They're sprouting up everywhere! This sensitive technology will not function while damaged.

non la.name: Non La
non la.description: This conical straw hat is useful for full sun protection, as well as carrying stuff!

minor otherworldly bait.name: Minor Otherworldly Bait
minor otherworldly bait.description: This is bait for fishing. Equip a fishing rod and then use this bait on water that you are standing next to in order to start fishing. This bait actually travels through a wormhole into a dark dimension and catches things there, instead of in the water. Minorly bad things.

lesser otherworldly bait.name: Lesser Otherworldly Bait
lesser otherworldly bait.description: This is bait for fishing. Equip a fishing rod and then use this bait on water that you are standing next to in order to start fishing. This bait actually travels through a wormhole into a dark dimension and catches things there, instead of in the water. Lesser bad things.

penguin mask.name: Penguin Mask
penguin mask.description: Wanna be as COOL as Master Peng? Not gonna happen. But you can wear this mask and look like a dork.

mini-peng.name: Mini-Peng
mini-peng.description: Master Peng is so swift, he can appear to be in multiple at once. But in the extra places, he looks very small.

popcorn.name: Popcorn
popcorn.description: Uh oh, drama! Somebody bust out the popcorn.

wasabi peas.name: Wasabi Peas
wasabi peas.description: Yowza, those are some spicy peas!

present goblin disguise.name: Present Goblin Disguise
present goblin disguise.description: Disguises you as a Present Goblin, bringer of joy.

stuff-4-toys box.name: Stuff-4-Toys Box
stuff-4-toys box.description: Drop stuff in here, and we'll donate toys to needy Growtopians!

letter block - zerp.name: Letter Block - Zerp
letter block - zerp.description: This is a letter block, like you played when you were a kid! This particular one has the letter Zerp on it. But I don't need to tell you that, you can just read it.

letter block - forg.name: Letter Block - Forg
letter block - forg.description: This is a letter block, like you played when you were a kid! This particular one has the letter Forg on it. But I don't need to tell you that, you can just read it.

letter block - wump.name: Letter Block - Wump
letter block - wump.description: This is a letter block, like you played when you were a kid! This particular one has the letter Wump on it. But I don't need to tell you that, you can just read it.

letter block - doozle.name: Letter Block - Doozle
letter block - doozle.description: This is a letter block, like you played when you were a kid! This particular one has the letter Doozle on it. But I don't need to tell you that, you can just read it.

hideous holiday sweater.name: Hideous Holiday Sweater
hideous holiday sweater.description: Your grandma thinks you look adorable in this.

winter turtleneck.name: Winter Turtleneck
winter turtleneck.description: Celebrate Winterfest in cozy style, with no worries of chin-freeze.

yo-yo.name: Yo-Yo
yo-yo.description: It's a disk on a string. Try smacking stuff with it!

meh, bunny suit.name: Meh, Bunny Suit
meh, bunny suit.description: MrMehMeh stores the carrots he eats here.

rubber band airplane.name: Rubber Band Airplane
rubber band airplane.description: Toss it and see where it goes! It'll smash if it hits any blocks, so aim carefully. Tap the direction you want to throw it. The further from yourself you tap, the harder you throw.

stuff-4-toys shirt.name: Stuff-4-Toys Shirt
stuff-4-toys shirt.description: Stuff-4-Toys is offering these stylish t-shirts to all Silver level donators!

present goblin home edition.name: Present Goblin Home Edition
present goblin home edition.description: Dress up as a Present Goblin for fun! You won't automatically drop presents, but its festive year-round! This costume overrides all other clothing, but if you don't like tossing tennis balls, try equipping other sportsballs with it!

solsascarf.name: Solsascarf
solsascarf.description: Solsagann is tossing out yesterday's baguettes! They are quite stale.

stuff-4-toys tote bag.name: Stuff-4-Toys Tote Bag
stuff-4-toys tote bag.description: Tote around your shopping with our fabulous tote bag. It lets everybody know you are serious about donating Stuff for Toys.

betty bluetooth doll.name: Betty Bluetooth Doll
betty bluetooth doll.description: This high-tech doll is the big craze this Winterfest! Everybody wants a remote-controlled doll that fires deadly lightning bolts!

surg-e.name: Surg-E
surg-e.description: This robot is amazingly accurate human analog (just look at it). Capable of simulating a wide range of disease and trauma condition. Place it anywhere and wrench it to perform surgery just like a human being. Since you have to cut into it, it's only usable once, win or lose!

caduceus.name: Caduceus
caduceus.description: This symbol is your reward for saving someone with surgery. You can trade them for rare surgical prizes by calling Sales-Man on your Telephone at 53785. Double-tap this in your inventory to combine 100 of them into a Golden Caduceus.

golden caduceus.name: Golden Caduceus
golden caduceus.description: This is worth 100 Caducei (that's the plural of Caduceus, I looked it up!). Double-tap this in your inventory to break one back into 100 Caducei. You can trade these for rare surgical prizes by calling Sales-Man on your telephone at 53785.

golden dragon statue.name: Golden Dragon Statue
golden dragon statue.description: Congratulations, you won the Grand Tournament!

silver dragon statue.name: Silver Dragon Statue
silver dragon statue.description: Congratulations, you placed in the top 3 of the Grand Tournament!

jade dragon statue.name: Jade Dragon Statue
jade dragon statue.description: Congratulations, you placed in the top 10 of the Grand Tournament!

surgical pins.name: Surgical Pins
surgical pins.description: Used only in surgery. When a bone is absolutely shattered,you need to use pins to put it back together. A Surgical Splint won't do it! Can only be used once you've opened an incision, of course.

surgical transfusion.name: Surgical Transfusion
surgical transfusion.description: Used only in surgery. If a patient's blood supply gets dangerously low, this will fill 'er up!

surgical defibrillator.name: Surgical Defibrillator
surgical defibrillator.description: Used only in surgery. If a patient's heart stops (which can happen when they are anesthetized), zap them with this to fire it up again.

surgical clamp.name: Surgical Clamp
surgical clamp.description: Used only in surgery.this can reduce a patient's bleeding significantly, but without closing up their incisions, like Surgical Stitches will do. You can only use this when you have open incisions.

surgical ultrasound.name: Surgical Ultrasound
surgical ultrasound.description: Used only in surgery. This detailed scan can inform you of any broken bones, tumors, or other physical issues within the patient's body. Use this right away to diagnose the problem!

surgical lab kit.name: Surgical Lab Kit
surgical lab kit.description: Used only in surgery. This kit will identify different microbes that could be present in the patient. Use it right away to diagnose any bacterial or viral issues. You cannot use Surgical Antibiotics until you've used a Lab Kit to identify the bacteria you're fighting.

empty surgery tray.name: Empty Surgery Tray
empty surgery tray.description: Not a real item, just used for an icon.

autoclave.name: Autoclave
autoclave.description: Wrench this device to clean your surgical instruments. And by "clean", we mean exchange 20 of one instrument for 1 of every other instrument.

biotronic brain enhancer.name: Biotronic Brain Enhancer
biotronic brain enhancer.description: This advanced cybernetic technology will increase your mental capacity, granting you 50% more XP (on average) for half an hour.

plague doctor mask.name: Plague Doctor Mask
plague doctor mask.description: There was a time when actual medical professionals would go out on the streets wearing this. It was a creepy, creepy time.

plague doctor hat.name: Plague Doctor Hat
plague doctor hat.description: Rumpled and trumpy, really showing your dedication to your craft.

plague doctor robe.name: Plague Doctor Robe
plague doctor robe.description: This robe is intended to protect you from pestilence. Sadly it was invented in pre-scientific times, so all it really protects you from is cold weather.

living dead remote.name: Living Dead Remote
living dead remote.description: You just couldn't accept your patients' deaths. And now you've created an abomination, haven't you? What has your foul science wrought?!

spare body part.name: Spare Body Part
spare body part.description: Oh, nobody's even gonna notice this is missing, I'm sure. They had at least two of these when they came in.

spare body.name: Spare Body
spare body.description: Wow, you had all the right parts to make a spare body! You never know when this might come in handy.

limb connector.name: Limb Connector
limb connector.description: This horrible twisted spikey thing could surely jam some limbs together if you needed to do that. For some reason.

massive fang.name: Massive Fang
massive fang.description: Imagine the size of the wolf this came from!

howler.name: Howler
howler.description: This seemingly harmless statue actually launches deadly sonic blasts. Wrench it to set the rate of fire! You can place as many Howlers as you like, but only 10 blasts can exist at a time, so if you have a lot, most of them will just sit there.

gemmin' juice.name: Gemmin' Juice
gemmin' juice.description: Got your mind on your gems and your gems on your mind? Start sippin' on Gemmin' Juice! It gives you a 10% chance of getting double gems from any blocks you break for 30 minutes. Consumed when used.

wolf skull shoulders.name: Wolf Skull Shoulders
wolf skull shoulders.description: Three heads are better than one, even if two of them are empty and skinless.

wolf gate.name: Wolf Gate
wolf gate.description: Punch it to open or shut it! Anybody unluck enough to be caught inside when it closes gets wolfed down.

wolf ticket.name: Wolf Ticket
wolf ticket.description: This ticket is your reward for completing Wolfworld. You can trade them for rare Wolfworld prizes by calling Sales-Man on your Telephone at 53785. Double-tap this in your inventory to combine 100 of them into an Enchanted Wolf Ticket.

enchanted wolf ticket.name: Enchanted Wolf Ticket
enchanted wolf ticket.description: This is worth 100 Wolf Tickets. Double-tap this in your inventory to break one back into 100 Wolf Tickets. You can trade this for rare Wolfworld prizes by calling Sales-Man on your Telephone at 53785.

sales-man standee.name: Sales-Man Standee
sales-man standee.description: The perfect way to advertise your wares - with a cardboard cut-out of Sales-Man himself! Scientifically proven to drive conversions and increase ROI.

sales shades.name: Sales Shades
sales shades.description: Cover your eyes, the savings are simply too glorious to behold!

ghost wolf monocle.name: Ghost Wolf Monocle
ghost wolf monocle.description: This monocle is haunted by the spirit of an ancient wolf! That's more common than you'd expect among monocles.

challenge of fenrir.name: Challenge of Fenrir
challenge of fenrir.description: Your progress in the Wolfworld has caused Fenrir himself to challenge you! Use this summons on All Howl's Eve to enter the halls of Valhowla. Once inside, you'll have only 3 minutes to search for the 4 treasures. Also don't forget Climbing Boots and a light source!

party screamer.name: Party Screamer
party screamer.description: Blow this horn to let everybody know where the party is! It's like a super broadcast, only you can't control what you say, because this party be OFF THE CHIZZY!!

valhowla treasure.name: Valhowla Treasure
valhowla treasure.description: Treasures for players to collect in Valhowla.

party popper.name: Party Popper
party popper.description: Get the party started with a blast of streamers!

party bunting.name: Party Bunting
party bunting.description: Dress the place up a little for our anniversary party!

party fowl.name: Party Fowl
party fowl.description: Whoa dude, major party fowl. You earned this for playing Growtopia for THREE YEARS, and over 100 hours, and reaching level 50! Wow, that's dedication.

iiii block.name: IIII Block
iiii block.description: Its Growtopia's fourth anniversary! Celebrate with this classic pewter-plated design reminiscent of the Roman numeral 4. Yes you can write 4 as IIII instead of IV , that's a real thing!

party cake.name: Party Cake
party cake.description: This tastes so good it just makes you want to dance!

head bangin' steel wolf.name: Head Bangin' Steel Wolf
head bangin' steel wolf.description: This robotic wolf rocks hard. Punch to activate, wrench to adjust settings.

pink bunting.name: Pink Bunting
pink bunting.description: Fancy the place up a little with some lovely pink fabric.

blue bunting.name: Blue Bunting
blue bunting.description: Fancy the place up a little with some lovely pink fabric.

white bunting.name: White Bunting
white bunting.description: Fancy the place up a little with some lovely pink fabric.

green bunting.name: Green Bunting
green bunting.description: Fancy the place up a little with some lovely pink fabric.

yellow bunting.name: Yellow Bunting
yellow bunting.description: Fancy the place up a little with some lovely pink fabric.

red & white awning.name: Red ? White Awning
red & white awning.description: These are surprisingly bouncy. Hold Jump as you land for maximum bounce.

green & yellow awning.name: Green ? Yellow Awning
green & yellow awning.description: These are surprisingly bouncy. Hold Jump as you land for maximum bounce.

blue awning.name: Blue Awning
blue awning.description: These are surprisingly bouncy. Hold Jump as you land for maximum bounce.

black awning.name: Black Awning
black awning.description: These are surprisingly bouncy. Hold Jump as you land for maximum bounce.

heart awning.name: Heart Awning
heart awning.description: These are surprisingly bouncy. Hold Jump as you land for maximum bounce.

pink cat as a hat.name: Pink Cat As A Hat
pink cat as a hat.description: Oh, the places you'll go wearing this hat! You can wear it on the train, or in the rain, or... well, actually don't wear it in the rain, it'll shrink.

blue cat as a hat.name: Blue Cat As A Hat
blue cat as a hat.description: Oh, the places you'll go wearing this hat! You can wear it on the train, or in the rain, or... well, actually don't wear it in the rain, it'll shrink.

grey cat as a hat.name: Grey Cat As A Hat
grey cat as a hat.description: Oh, the places you'll go wearing this hat! You can wear it on the train, or in the rain, or... well, actually don't wear it in the rain, it'll shrink.

orange cat as a hat.name: Orange Cat As A Hat
orange cat as a hat.description: Oh, the places you'll go wearing this hat! You can wear it on the train, or in the rain, or... well, actually don't wear it in the rain, it'll shrink.

gruel.name: Gruel
gruel.description: This bland flavorless mush is not delicious. The only nice thing about it is that you can feed it to a Silkworm without changing its color!

pegasus.name: Pegasus
pegasus.description: If you were a pegasus, you'd spend all your time flying too. Why walk on those teeny legs? These mighty wings allow you both to double jump too.

golden pegasus.name: Golden Pegasus
golden pegasus.description: If you were a pegasus, you'd spend all your time flying too. Why walk on those teeny legs? These mighty wings allow you both to double jump too.

heart glasses.name: Heart Glasses
heart glasses.description: The world just looks like a lovelier place through these rose-colored glasses.

loveseat.name: Loveseat
loveseat.description: Legs getting tired? Have a seat!

golden heart glasses.name: Golden Heart Glasses
golden heart glasses.description: The world just looks like a more expensive place through these gold-tinted glasses.

chocolate heart.name: Chocolate Heart
chocolate heart.description: Chocolate heals all wounds. Emotional wounds that is. It is pretty useless for broken bones. And really it doesn't do much for emotional problems either, it just tastes good.

ruby shard.name: Ruby Shard
ruby shard.description: Watch out, this is a really sharp fragment of Ruby. It seems strangely magnetically attracted to other shards like it. Maybe if you got 200 of the together, they'd fuse into something! Yeah, that's how reality works!

ruby lock.name: Ruby Lock
ruby lock.description: Locks an entire world. And looks lovely doing it. There's a 1% chance each day that a rock in the world will become Heartstone!

chemsynth processor.name: Chemsynth Processor
chemsynth processor.description: Place a row of 10 Chemsynth Tanks to the right of this machine, and then wrench it to use GrowTech's new synthetic chemical creation technology! Patent pending.

chemsynth tank.name: Chemsynth Tank
chemsynth tank.description: You'll need to attach this to the right side of a Chemsynth Processor to get any use out of it. You'll need 10 attached to a Chemsynth Processor, in fact.

chemsynth centrifuge.name: Chemsynth Centrifuge
chemsynth centrifuge.description: Use on a highlighted Chemsynth Tank to rotate chemicals around it. Rotates as many from the right as it can to match how many are to the left of the selected Tank.

chemsynth replicator.name: Chemsynth Replicator
chemsynth replicator.description: Use on a highlighted Chemsynth Tank to duplicate its contents, pushing all chemicals to the right to make room.

chemsynth catalyst.name: Chemsynth Catalyst
chemsynth catalyst.description: Use on a highlighted Chemsynth Tank to shift its color upward on the spectrum (Red, Yellow, Green, Blue, Pink, Red). This also affects all touching tanks of the same color.

chemsynth solvent.name: Chemsynth Solvent
chemsynth solvent.description: Use on a highlighted Chemsynth Tank to dissolve it, shifting chemicals left to fill in the gap. A random chemical is added to the rightmost tank.

chemsynth stirrer.name: Chemsynth Stirrer
chemsynth stirrer.description: Use on a highlighted Chemsynth Tank to swap the chemicals on either side of it with each other. The selected tank is unaffected.

synthetic chemical.name: Synthetic Chemical
synthetic chemical.description: This chemical was created in a lab. Its properties are virtually untested!

gruesome marker.name: Gruesome Marker
gruesome marker.description: Use these sort of like Doors

skeletal throne.name: Skeletal Throne
skeletal throne.description: Looks like you're the new king of the zombies! Or somebody with four legs died here.

zombie brain.name: Zombie Brain
zombie brain.description: Ew, this is a brain that popped out of a zombie's head! Maybe sales-man wants it, You sure don't. Double-tap this in your inventory to combine 100 of them into a Pile Of Zombie Brains!

pile of zombie brains.name: Pile of Zombie Brains
pile of zombie brains.description: Ew, this is a brain that popped out of a zombie's head! Maybe Sales-Man wants it. You sure don't. Double-tap this in your inventory to split it up into 100 Zombie Brains.

mutated seed core.name: Mutated Seed Core
mutated seed core.description: This is an immature mutated seed. It'll mature into a mutated seed if you log out and back in!

zombie defense force helmet.name: Zombie Defense Force Helmet
zombie defense force helmet.description: This helmet covers your vital brain region from zombie attack. Unfortunately, zombies only need to punch you to infect you, so it's not terribly useful.

zombie defense force uniform.name: Zombie Defense Force Uniform
zombie defense force uniform.description: This is the official uniform of the Zombie Defense Force! It has lots of pockets for your lip balm, candy, paper clips, and other key zombie-fighting tools.

zombie defense force pants.name: Zombie Defense Force Pants
zombie defense force pants.description: You could just wear any green pants and you probably won't get in trouble, but these have a cool Z logo sewn into the inside waistband.

camouflage facepaint.name: Camouflage Facepaint
camouflage facepaint.description: They'll never see you coming. Unless they look anywhere other than your face. At least you might freak them out - "Ah, it's a guy with no face!!"

ak-8087.name: AK-8087
ak-8087.description: The ultimate zombie-slaying weapon. Or pumpkin-slaying.

barricaded door.name: Barricaded Door
barricaded door.description: This door has been barricaded, so zombies can't get through it, only normal Growtopians! Place one and then use your Wrench on it to set the destination.

infected door.name: Infected Door
infected door.description: Yuck, this door has horrible zombie slime on it. Nobody but a zombie would dare enter it. Place one and then use your Wrench on it to set the destination.

zombie sign.name: Zombie Sign
zombie sign.description: This sign is written in Zombese, so humans can't read it, only zombies!

retinal scan data repository.name: Retinal Scan Data Repository
retinal scan data repository.description: This data system can store useful information, but the retinal scan prevents zombies from accessing it. Only humans can!

skull launcher.name: Skull Launcher
skull launcher.description: The ultimate zombie weapon. Actually, the only zombie weapon - you can use this while you're a zombie! (Also usable by humans)

rainbow kite.name: Rainbow Kite
rainbow kite.description: The most colourful kite in all of Growtopia!

zombie hound.name: Zombie Hound
zombie hound.description: Braaainnss! This little puppy just wants to play! Or maybe he's hungry... hmmm...

crazy zombie hair.name: Crazy Zombie Hair
crazy zombie hair.description: The undead use a lot of hairspray.

objective marker.name: Objective Marker
objective marker.description: Use these sort of like Doors - They have IDs, so Doors can lead to them, though you can't travel from them. Use your wrench to set their ID.

infected block.name: Infected Block
infected block.description: This block is pulsing with g-Virus infection. It should be safe to smash, just wash your hands afterward.

weather machine - apocalypse.name: Weather Machine - Apocalypse
weather machine - apocalypse.description: Feeling nostalgic for the end of the world? Let's bring it back! With this weather active, somebody in your world will get infected with the g-Virus every hour, and players can kill zombies in your world, with the appropriate weapon. This sensitive technology will not function while damaged.

g-virus info sign.name: g-Virus Info Sign
g-virus info sign.description: Anybody can wrench this sign to see the current status of the g-Virus epidemic. Remember to wash your hands!

mutated cell.name: Mutated Cell
mutated cell.description: Strange mutated cells collected during the Zombie Apocalypse. If you combine 200 of them, you might be able to create new mutant life...

chainlink fence.name: Chainlink Fence
chainlink fence.description: The flimsiest and cheapest way to keep zombies out. Unfortunately this fence is in front of Growtopia, so it only keeps zombies from getting into the game from outside of the screen, which is a pretty unlikely situation.

z.d.f. fence.name: Z.D.F. Fence
z.d.f. fence.description: Let the zombies know what they're in for if they trample your fence! The Z.D.F is ready to rumble!

rusted chainlink fence.name: Rusted Chainlink Fence
rusted chainlink fence.description: It won't take zombies long to get through this fence!

commercial oven.name: Commercial Oven
commercial oven.description: Real chefs do their cooking in Growtech ovens like this - 2 bays, with individual heat settings up to 11,00 K. And a warning drawer! Wrench it for information.

chef's whites.name: Chef's Whites
chef's whites.description: Spotless! Until you actually start cooking.

chef's cap.name: Chef's Cap
chef's cap.description: A real chef doesn't wear the big poofy hat... this cap keeps your hair out of your eyes and out of the food without catching on fire regularly.

chef's pants.name: Chef's Pants
chef's pants.description: These are made of plastex polymer... all the sauce you spill on them just rolls right off! Onto your shoes.

butcher knife.name: Butcher Knife
butcher knife.description: This heavy blade is perfect to hacking through bones. Use it on Cutting Board to chop up meat!

unearthly synthoid.name: Unearthly Synthoid
unearthly synthoid.description: It's completely synthetic life! Not of this Earth!

radioactive synthoid.name: Radioactive Synthoid
radioactive synthoid.description: It's completely synthetic life! Burning with radiation!

mysterious synthoid.name: Mysterious Synthoid
mysterious synthoid.description: It's completely synthetic life! How mysterious!

haunted synthoid.name: Haunted Synthoid
haunted synthoid.description: It's completely synthetic life! Possessed with synthetic unlife!

untrade-a-box.name: Untrade-a-Box
untrade-a-box.description: This amazing box can store all those pesky untradable items! Only the World Lock owner can use it, and the World Lock can't be traded or destroyed while an Untrade-a-Box is in the world.

wobbly dress.name: Wobbly Dress
wobbly dress.description: It's difficult to tell whether Bungbi's dress is made of candy, or just styled to look like it...

lucky portal.name: Lucky Portal
lucky portal.description: This portal isn't actually lucky unless you set a destination for it that is lucky. So it's really up to you!

lucky kitty.name: Lucky Kitty
lucky kitty.description: This kitty sits in your world, constantly waving, and reminding you of how lucky you are to have a kitty in your world.

bamboo.name: Bamboo
bamboo.description: Bamboo is a sign of luck. It's also a grass!

ladybug leaf.name: Ladybug Leaf
ladybug leaf.description: Ladybugs are considered lucky, so consider yourself lucky that you found this sweet leaf that's making one follow you around!

cosmic rain.name: Cosmic Rain
cosmic rain.description: This is what the call "hard radiation". That of course means it's solid so you can't jump up through it, you can however drop down, since it's moving down!

shamrock hair pin.name: Shamrock Hair Pin
shamrock hair pin.description: Carry the luck of the Irish on your head!

golden razor wings.name: Golden Razor Wings
golden razor wings.description: Slice through the air with the greatest of ease! And double jump.

cosmic sky horse.name: Cosmic Sky Horse
cosmic sky horse.description: This winged beast hails from a distant star system. Those mighty wings let you move fast, but they're not strong enough to double jump (living in space has atrophied its muscles).

bridle design.name: Bridle Design
bridle design.description: This paper details a method for forging a bridle out of Star Iron. If you forge 100 Star Iron Ingots with this design in hand, you'll make a Cosmic Bridle. This consumes the design.

star iron.name: Star Iron
star iron.description: This is raw ore, mined from the heart of a comet. Surely there's something you can do with it!

star iron ingot.name: Star Iron Ingot
star iron ingot.description: You've managed to process this ore into a pure, shining ingot, just by tossing into a fire!

cosmic bridle.name: Cosmic Bridle
cosmic bridle.description: I'm pretty sure this bridle is some kind of alien technology. Now what can you do with it?

hover platform.name: Hover Platform
hover platform.description: Cosmic energy keeps these platforms aloft. Who knows what keeps the wooden ones up?

spaceman pants.name: Spaceman Pants
spaceman pants.description: I don't know why, but most alien creatures insist on wearing clothes made of tin foil.

spaceman suit.name: Spaceman Suit
spaceman suit.description: I don't know why, but most alien creatures insist on wearing clothes made of tin foil.

synthetic oculum.name: Synthetic Oculum
synthetic oculum.description: The human eye sees a limited spectrum. Replace yours with these synthetic models! They transmit data direct to your central cortex. Unfortunately they also make you look cross-eyed.

cranial lagomorph.name: Cranial Lagomorph
cranial lagomorph.description: Don't be alarmed, but there may be a bunny on your head...

cardboard egg.name: Cardboard Egg
cardboard egg.description: It's a classic photo op! Stand behind it and pretend you're a newly hatched chick. Fun for the whole family!

salsa.name: Salsa
salsa.description: This item doesn't really exist, it's just for cooking.

flour.name: Flour
flour.description: We've ground it up, and bleached out all the nutrients! It's not really edible anymore, but it's a key ingredient in deliciousness.

lettuce.name: Lettuce
lettuce.description: Crisp and green, no calories, no flavor. Just like we like it!

salt block.name: Salt Block
salt block.description: Deer like to lick this. The pink coloration in it is from trace minerals in the salt.

salt.name: Salt
salt.description: The greatest thing since sliced bread - and even sliced bread would be pretty bad without some salt in it.

pepper.name: Pepper
pepper.description: Would you be surprised to learn that this is a fruit? It's true!

sugar.name: Sugar
sugar.description: Pro-tip: if you can resist it, never ever eat this substance. It is very unhealthy. But it's sooooo gooood.

disgusting mess.name: Disgusting Mess
disgusting mess.description: This abomination is what happens when you let video gamers cook. Do NOT eat.

bland mush.name: Bland Mush
bland mush.description: This is not even food. Nobody would eat this.

beef.name: Beef
beef.description: A big ol' juice T-bone. Well, an O-Bone. Is that a thing?

food grinder.name: Food Grinder
food grinder.description: The high speed blades and crushers in this device can grind up some foods into more ground-up foods! Just tap your food on the Food Grinder to begin.

pepper tree.name: Pepper Tree
pepper tree.description: The spiciest of trees. Well, I guess there's also cinnamon. Probably a lot of spices grow on trees, huh? I regret this entire description.

bacon.name: Bacon
bacon.description: Bacon. It's raw though, don't eat it.

chicken meat.name: Chicken Meat
chicken meat.description: This item is often known as Chick Of The Land. According to mermaids.

zraei's dragoscarf.name: Zraei's Dragoscarf
zraei's dragoscarf.description: When a normal scarf isn't enough... This DragoScarf will assist you, granting Enhanced Digging, but only if you don't have it already. Sponsored by Bretz and Zraei - first to complete all epic quests!

homemade fish taco.name: Homemade Fish Taco
homemade fish taco.description: Homemade Baja taste, with fresh pico de gallo. Food Buff: Gain 1 gem for every 5lbs. your fish catches weigh.

apple strudel.name: Apple Strudel
apple strudel.description: Fresh from the oven! Food Buff: Trees you plant grow 5% faster.

berry crepes.name: Berry Crepes
berry crepes.description: It's the really thin pancakes you love so much! Just say it! Food Buff: 30% more XP earned from Surgery.

bbq bacon burger.name: BBQ Bacon Burger
bbq bacon burger.description: The king of burgers. Food Buff: Get 50 gems for every villain you defeat.

beer-battered fish and chips.name: Beer-Battered Fish And Chips
beer-battered fish and chips.description: Deep fried goodness. Food Buff: Catch 5% larger fish.

onion.name: Onion
onion.description: Ah, don't cry. It's just a vegetable.

arroz con pollo.name: Arroz Con Pollo
arroz con pollo.description: In English, that's rice with chicken. Creative! Food Buff: 10% chance of a gem everytime you break a block.

egg wallpaper.name: Egg Wallpaper
egg wallpaper.description: Bring the springtime indoors with our classic line of wallpapers.

mini mallard.name: Mini Mallard
mini mallard.description: Ducks instinctively follow their mothers around. This one just follows you because it's tied to your wrist, though.

baking chocolate.name: Baking Chocolate
baking chocolate.description: This chocolate is ready for all your baking needs! It's not sweet though, don't eat it.

mac n' cheese star.name: Mac n' Cheese Star
mac n' cheese star.description: Your reward for incredible cooking skill! You can trade them for cooking prizes by calling Sales-Man on your Telephone at 53785. Double-Tap this in your inventory to combine 100 of them together.

plethora of mac n' cheese stars.name: Plethora Of Mac n' Cheese Stars
plethora of mac n' cheese stars.description: This is worth 100 Mac n' Cheese Stars. Not even Growdon Ramsley has this many! Double-tap this in your inventory to break one down into 100 Stars. You can trade these for rare cooking prizes by calling Sales-Man on your Telephone at 53785.

mac n' cheese star block.name: Mac n' Cheese Star Block
mac n' cheese star block.description: Now you can decorate your world with Mac N' Cheese Stars! Show off your incredible cooking skill.

home oven.name: Home Oven
home oven.description: Toss in some food and cook it up! This oven actually works! Wrench it for info.

master chef's oven.name: Master Chef's Oven
master chef's oven.description: This oven is custom-built for you because of your incredible cooking skill. It works so well, you can be lazy - it will produce edible food at 50% quality or higher. Wrench it for information.

chemist's goggles.name: Chemist's Goggles
chemist's goggles.description: The perfect eyewear for doing chemistry! Grants a 10% chance to not consume a chemical when you use a Chemsynth tool.

marshmallow.name: Marshmallow
marshmallow.description: Bouncy and delicious. Hold Jump as you land for maximum bounce.

txmom's crown.name: TXMom's Crown
txmom's crown.description: Be honored to wear this beautiful crown. Sponsored by TXMom.

kudo's carriage.name: Kudo's Carriage
kudo's carriage.description: This thing goes pretty fast for a vehicle with only 2 horsepower. Sponsored by Kudobelle.

audio gear.name: Audio Gear
audio gear.description: Wanna get crazy with music? This solid block works like Sheet Music, but with your Wrench, you can adjust the volume and play up to 5 simulataneous notes.

audio rack.name: Audio Rack
audio rack.description: Wanna get crazy with music? Tis passable block works like Sheet Music, but with your Wrench, you can adjust the volume and play up to 5 simultaneous notes.

sheet music: sax note.name: Sheet Music: Sax Note
sheet music: sax note.description: If you aren't in range of a Boombox, this will play a saxophone note for you. Put it in different places for different pitches.

sheet music: sharp sax.name: Sheet Music: Sharp Sax
sheet music: sharp sax.description: This plays a half-step higher than Sheet Music: Sax Note.

sheet music: flat sax.name: Sheet Music: Flat Sax
sheet music: flat sax.description: This plays a half-step lower note than Sheet Music: Sax Note.

sheet music: repeat begin.name: Sheet Music: Repeat Begin
sheet music: repeat begin.description: This marks where your song should begin repeating. You'll need a Sheet Music: Repeat End in the same row to actually repeat. You can add more pairs in other rows to repeat multiple times, or repeat other sections.

sheet music: repeat end.name: Sheet Music: Repeat End
sheet music: repeat end.description: This marks where your song should repeat a section. The music marker will jump back to the most recent Sheet Music: Repeat Begin that's in the same row (or the beginning of the song if not). If you need to repeat a section more than once, put Repeat pairs in multiple rows.

saxamaphone.name: Saxamaphone
saxamaphone.description: You can't punch when holding this, you're too busy ROCKING! Punch anywhere to play music. If you punch to your left or right, you can bend the note higher or lower. Punch in your own column to play the same notes that Sheet Music: Sax Note plays.

hazmat boots.name: Hazmat Boots
hazmat boots.description: In case of hazardous spills, you'll want a pair of these! Reduces lava damage by 50%.

hazmat pants.name: Hazmat Pants
hazmat pants.description: Don't get a tear in these, or you'll be exposed to whatever lurks outside!

hazmat suit.name: Hazmat Suit
hazmat suit.description: This suit protects you from any sort of biochemical leaks. Or it would if you had zipped it up right. Yikes, good thing this was just a test!

hazmat helmet.name: Hazmat Helmet
hazmat helmet.description: Protects your precious face from exposure to harmful stuff.

geiger charger.name: Geiger Charger
geiger charger.description: Tap a Geiger Counter in here to charge it up! It's half the speed of hand-charging, but it's convenient. Punch to retrieve it when it's ready.

uranium necklace.name: Uranium Necklace
uranium necklace.description: Wearing this will dramatically reduce your lifespan, but you'll be looking GOOD until it's over!

uranium block.name: Uranium Block
uranium block.description: This block might be slowly making you sick. Surely there are better things you could be building with.

confetti cannon.name: Confetti Cannon
confetti cannon.description: Precision telescopic sights ensure you deliver lethal payload directly to center mass.

hotpants.name: Hotpants
hotpants.description: You look hot in these. And so does your pet jalapeo!

corn.name: Corn
corn.description: This is what it's like before you pop it.

corn meal.name: Corn Meal
corn meal.description: This corn has been crushed into a pile of dust.

avocado.name: Avocado
avocado.description: This mushy green-black blob is actually a citrus fruit. What horrors hath nature wrought.

chips and guacamole.name: Chips And Guacamole
chips and guacamole.description: Crunchy and gooshy. Food Buff: 50 gems for every victory against a Pet Trainer.

green geiger v-neck.name: Green Geiger V-Neck
green geiger v-neck.description: This shirt is made out of... stuff.

blue geiger v-neck.name: Blue Geiger V-Neck
blue geiger v-neck.description: This shirt is made out of... stuff.

purple geiger v-neck.name: Purple Geiger V-Neck
purple geiger v-neck.description: This shirt is made out of... stuff.

orange geiger v-neck.name: Orange Geiger V-Neck
orange geiger v-neck.description: This shirt is made out of... stuff.

xenoid suit.name: Xenoid Suit
xenoid suit.description: This skin-tight suit really makes you look like a freaky alien.

xenoid mask.name: Xenoid Mask
xenoid mask.description: You seriously look like a freaky alien.

xenoid claws.name: Xenoid Claws
xenoid claws.description: These nasty claws makes you look like a freaky alien.

xenoid leggings.name: Xenoid Leggings
xenoid leggings.description: These skin-tight leggings make you look like a freaky alien.

xenoid shoes.name: Xenoid Shoes
xenoid shoes.description: These awkward pointy heels make you look like a freaky alien.

villain portrait - h.r. geiger.name: Villain Portrait - H.R. Geiger
villain portrait - h.r. geiger.description: Just before knocking him unconscious, you snapped a lovely photo of Bunny Barko for posterity. Put it up on the wall, show off your achievement!

superpower - alien egg.name: Superpower - Alien Egg
superpower - alien egg.description: This is a Rare Ice Superpower Card for use in fighting crime. You can also place it as a block! Card effect: Implant an egg in your foe. If they repeat an element during the next four turns, it bursts for 5 damage!

locked adventure door.name: Locked Adventure Door
locked adventure door.description: This door can be walked through by anyone holding an Adventure Item - Key.

adventure rope piton.name: Adventure Rope Piton
adventure rope piton.description: Install this right next to walls. If a player is holding an Adventure Item - Rope, they can climb the wall.

ancient block.name: Ancient Block
ancient block.description: It's amazing how ancient Growtopians were able to carve such perfect blocks. Some say it was done by aliens! They're wrong.

adventure brazier.name: Adventure Brazier
adventure brazier.description: When a player who has Adventure Item - Torch steps on this, their torch is used up to light all braziers for 10 seconds. While its lit, all the Adventure Barriers in the world move in or out, just for that player.

adventure barrier.name: Adventure Barrier
adventure barrier.description: These blocks can be punched by the world owner to open or close them. But if a player lights an Adventure Brazier, they will be reversed for that player

adventure pedestal.name: Adventure Pedestal
adventure pedestal.description: When a player who has Adventure Item - Golden Idol steps on this, their idol is placed on the pedestal, opening all Adventure Idol Gates in the world (for them only), or shutting ones that are open.

adventure idol gate.name: Adventure Idol Gate
adventure idol gate.description: These blocks can be punched by the world owner to open or close them. But if a player places an idol on an Adventure Pedestal, they will be reversed for that player - open ones will be shut, shut ones will be open.

angry adventure gorilla.name: Angry Adventure Gorilla
angry adventure gorilla.description: This gorilla will pummel anyone who gets close! But if you have an Adventure Item - Banana, you can punch him to give it to him, and sneak by while he is eating for 10 seconds.

minecart.name: Minecart
minecart.description: Nothing says adventure like riding around in a minecart! Tracks not included (but the wheels are modified to run on any surface).

adventure item - pineapple.name: Adventure Item - Pineapple
adventure item - pineapple.description: Place this in your world to be used in your Gateways To Adventure! Players can pick it up by punching it. They lose it if they leave your world.

mystery door.name: Mystery Door
mystery door.description: You can set up to 5 destinations for this door with your Wrench, and when a player enters it, they'll be sent randomly to any of them!

adventure checkpoint.name: Adventure Checkpoint
adventure checkpoint.description: If you die, you'll respawn at the last Checkpoint you touched!

the adventure begins.name: The Adventure Begins
the adventure begins.description: Wrench this to adjust settings for your adventure. When players step on it, all their adventure items are reset, and you can assign them limited lives or a timer to complete the adventure.

mariachi hat.name: Mariachi Hat
mariachi hat.description: Not only does this fancy hat cover your head from the heat, it also makes you look amazing while you sing and dance.

mariachi suit.name: Mariachi Suit
mariachi suit.description: Look the part while playing your guitar like a true musician of Mexico.

seductive rose.name: Seductive Rose
seductive rose.description: Sticking a rose in your mouth seems to make your voice so much more attractive when you sing.

red brimmed hat.name: Red Brimmed Hat
red brimmed hat.description: A party hat for the most sophisticated.

red formal dress.name: Red Formal Dress
red formal dress.description: The finest dress for all your fancy dress parties.

luchador announcer.name: Luchador Announcer
luchador announcer.description: A new challenger enters the ring! Summons the villain "El Peligro"...

adventure item - crystal goblet.name: Adventure Item - Crystal Goblet
adventure item - crystal goblet.description: Place this in your world to be used in your Gateways To Adventure! Players can pick it up by punching it. They lose it if they leave your world.
